The Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, has tested negative for the Covid-19 virus. Shehu, who urged everyone to continue self-isolation, said it was necessary to speak to ease the fears of friends and relatives. He prayed for Governor Nasir El-Rufai of Kaduna State to overcome the coronavirus infection in subsequent tweet.  The presidential media aide, in his Twitter handle@GarShehu, tweeted: “My test proved negative for the virus. Alhamdu Lillah! “Notwithstanding, I advise everyone that we continue the isolation and work from home. “I think it is only fair that I ease the fears of my friends and relations with whom I made recent contacts about the coronavirus. Fake news media had said all sorts of rubbish about me and the President I work for. “I join in prayers for Malam Nasiru to overcome the #Covid-19 infection.” Buhari releases aircraft for emergency operations COVID-19: Obaseki tests negative, remains in self-isolation COVID-19 exposure: Many govs refuse to self-isolate